    "visualization_explanation": "This treemap uses hierarchical data encoding with three structural levels: national total \u2192 regions \u2192 provinces/territories. Synthetic area values maintain real rank order while introducing 15% variance from official statistics (\u03bc=1.5M km\u00b2, \u03c3=1.2M). The squarified layout algorithm optimizes rectangle aspect ratios per Bruls et al.'s space-filling principles. Color progression from light blue (#d6eaf8) to dark navy (#2c3e50) encodes regional groupings while maintaining 3:1 contrast ratio for accessibility. Drill-down interactivity follows Shneiderman's mantra of overview-first with detail-on-demand. Tooltip percentage annotations provide temporal context through calculated variance from historical baselines."
